# JackSparrow Trading Agent - Cursor AI Project Rules

This file defines the coding standards, conventions, and best practices for the JackSparrow project.

## Project Overview

**Repository**: https://github.com/energyforreal/JackSparrow  
**Project Name**: JackSparrow Trading Agent

## Rule Organization

This project uses modular rule files in `.cursor/rules/` that are automatically loaded based on file patterns. Detailed standards are defined in:

- **Coding Standards**: `.cursor/rules/coding-standards.mdc` - Python and TypeScript/React code style
- **Naming Conventions**: `.cursor/rules/naming-conventions.mdc` - File, class, function naming
- **Error Handling**: `.cursor/rules/error-handling.mdc` - Error handling patterns
- **Logging Standards**: `.cursor/rules/logging-standards.mdc` - Structured logging with structlog
- **Testing Requirements**: `.cursor/rules/testing-requirements.mdc` - Test coverage and organization
- **Security Standards**: `.cursor/rules/security-standards.mdc` - Security best practices
- **Git Workflow**: `.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc` - Branch strategy and commit messages
- **ML Model Management**: `.cursor/rules/ml-model-management.mdc` - Model organization and MCP protocol
- **Documentation Organization**: `.cursor/rules/documentation-organization.mdc` - Documentation structure

## Key Project Standards (Summary)

- **Code Style**: PEP 8 for Python, Airbnb for TypeScript/React
- **Line Length**: Max 100 characters (soft limit 88)
- **Type Hints**: Always required for Python functions
- **Docstrings**: Google-style for Python, JSDoc for TypeScript
- **Test Coverage**: Minimum 80%, 100% for critical paths
- **Logging**: Use structlog with structured context fields
- **Git**: Conventional commits with branch strategy (main/develop/feature/*)

## Performance Targets

- API Response Time: p95 < 200ms
- WebSocket Latency: < 50ms
- Database Queries: < 100ms
- Feature Computation: < 500ms
- Model Inference: < 1000ms

## Operational Commands

- `start` - Launch all services (backend, agent, frontend)
- `restart` - Clean restart of all services
- `audit` - Run system audit (linting, tests, health checks)
- `error` - Quick error diagnostics

See `.cursor/commands/` for detailed command documentation.

